<H2><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C"><B>EUCHARISTIC PRAYER II (2): PREFACE</B></FONT></H2>
<H4><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C"><I>Capo 2</I></FONT></H4>
<H3><PRE>

</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">   Am         G     Am
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">P. The Lord be with you.
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">   G              Am
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">A. And with your Spirit.
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">                  G
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">P. Lift up your hearts.
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">                           Am
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">A. We lift them up to the Lord.
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">   G                                  Am
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">P. Let us give thanks to the Lord our God.
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">       G           Am
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">A. It is right and just.
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">            G                      Am
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">P. Truly it is our duty and our salvation
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">   G                                   Am
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   always and everywhere to give you thanks
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">                                     G      Am
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   Father, through your beloved Son, Jesus Christ.

</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   He is the Word
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">           G                   Am
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   through whom you made the universe,
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">                   F         Am
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   the Savior you sent to redeem us.
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">           G
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   By the power of the Holy Spirit,
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">                                            Am
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   He took flesh and was born of the Virgin Mary.
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">                    G                      Am
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   For our sake, He opened His arms on the cross;
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">       G             Am
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   He put an end to death
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">                G        Am
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   and revelead the resurrection.

</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">       Am       G        Am
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">A. AND REVEALED THE RESURRECTION. (2x)

</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">       G                      Am
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">P. In this He fulfilled your will
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">               G           Am
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   and won for you a holy people.
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">       G                         Am
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   And so we join the choirs of angels

</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   and with all the saints
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">   G                 Am
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#000000">   we proclaim your glory.

</PRE></H3>

<H4><FONT COLOR="#A13F3C">(to be followed by the “Holy” of the liturgical time)</FONT></H4>




